**CONFIDENTIAL ENGINEERING DOCUMENTATION**

# Table of Contents

# 1. Project Overview

MiOS (MiOS) is a self-replicating, immutable, cloud-native workstation OS built on Fedora Rawhide bootc. It ships GNOME 50 Wayland-only, full KVM/QEMU/VFIO GPU passthrough, Podman/K3s, Pacemaker/Corosync HA clustering, CrowdSec sovereign-mode IPS, Gamescope SteamOS-mode, and Waydroid Android. Everything baked at build time — zero post-install pulls. 47 tracked files, 2,769 lines of scripts, 19 system overlays, ~240 RPM packages, 5 Flatpaks.

Five deployment formats: RAW disk, VHDX (Hyper-V), WSL2 tarball, Anaconda ISO, OCI push to GHCR. GPU auto-detection at boot adapts for bare metal, Hyper-V, QEMU, or VMware. Same image boots everywhere.

## 1.1 Technology Stack

| **Layer** | **Technology** |
| --- | --- |
| Base OS | Fedora Rawhide bootc (fc45), ComposeFS + XFS/ext4, dnf5, systemd, SELinux |
| Desktop | GNOME 50 Tokyo (Wayland-only, Mutter 50, GTK 4.22, libadwaita 1.9, Geist font, Bibata cursor) |
| Virtualization | KVM/QEMU/libvirt, VFIO GPU passthrough, Looking Glass B7, edk2-ovmf, swtpm |
| Containers | Podman, Buildah, Skopeo, bootc, BIB, K3s Kubernetes |
| Gaming | Steam, Gamescope SteamOS GDM session, Wine, Lutris, Bottles, GameMode, MangoHud |
| HA Clustering | Pacemaker, Corosync, PCS, fence-agents, keepalived, haproxy, etcd |
| Security | CrowdSec (sovereign/offline), fapolicyd, USBGuard, firewalld (default-deny drop zone) |
| GPU | Mesa (AMD/Intel), NVIDIA akmod, ROCm, driverctl VFIO toggle, GPU auto-detect |
| Android | Waydroid with GAPPS |
| Registry | GHCR (ghcr.io/kabuki94/mios:latest) |

